theorem Topology.isClosed_boundary {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed (closure A \ interior A : Set X) := by
  -- `closure A` is closed.
  have h₁ : IsClosed (closure A) := isClosed_closure
  -- The complement of an open set is closed.
  have h₂ : IsClosed ((interior A)ᶜ : Set X) := (isOpen_interior.compl)
  -- The intersection of two closed sets is closed.
  have h_inter : IsClosed (closure A ∩ (interior A)ᶜ : Set X) := h₁.inter h₂
  -- Rewrite the intersection as a set difference.
  simpa [Set.diff_eq] using h_inter
